title: Pumping Mississippi River water west: solution or pipedream?
description: Amid a major drought in the Western U.S., a proposed solution comes up repeatedly: large-scale river diversions, including pumping Mississippi River water to parched states. Just this past summer, the idea caused a firestorm of letters to the editor at…
author: By BRITTNEY J. MILLER - Cedar Rapids Gazette

title: Fact check: Kari Lake's continuing false Arizona election claims
description: As she contemplates a run for the US Senate, Republican Kari Lake continues to make false claims about her loss in Arizona's 2022 gubernatorial election.
author: Daniel Dale

title: Utah governor signs major education funding bill, becoming third state to enshrine school choice into law
description: Utah Gov. Spencer Cox on Sunday signed a major school choice bill on Sunday, giving parents more options for their children’s education.
author: Joshua Nelson

title: Republicans worry Kari Lake and Blake Masters will lose Arizona Senate race again in 2024
description: Kari Lake and Blake Masters ran unsuccessful campaigns for state office in Arizona last year, aligning themselves closely to former President Trump.
author: Sophia Slacik

title: Kari Lake Shares Update on Election Case in Appeals Court
description: On Wednesday, a three-judge panel met to determine whether Lake's once-rejected lawsuit has a fighting chance for a second trial.
author: Katherine Fung

title: Arizona GOP bows to election denialism in bid for unity
description: Jeff DeWit, a former state treasurer and Trump campaign aide, wooed prominent election deniers to stave off far-right challenge
author: Yvonne Wingett Sanchez
